cs.LG, cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with the Sample Compression Conjecture, which is a problem in machine learning and computational geometry. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves combinatorial and graph-theoretic techniques, which suggest categories such as cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper uses geometric constructions and algorithms, which could fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
